                    "title": "RFK Jr. testifies before Congress amid HHS overhaul, Trump budget cuts",
                    "link": "https://www.axios.com/2025/05/14/rfk-testify-congress-hhs-layoffs-measles-outbreak",
                    "description": "<p>Health Secretary <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/14/rfk-jr-infant-formula-fda-review\" target=\"_blank\">Robert F. Kennedy Jr.</a> will testify on Capitol Hill Wednesday, where he's likely to be pressed on <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/07/hhs-rehire-laid-off-workers-kennedy\" target=\"_blank\">mass layoffs</a> to the Department of Health and Human Services, billions in cuts to the agencies he oversees and his handling of the measles outbreak.</p><p><strong>Why it matters: </strong>Kennedy's testimony before a House panel and the Senate Health, Education, Labor, and Pensions (HELP) Committee will mark his first time testifying before Congress since he was sworn in earlier this year.</p><hr><ul><li>The administration has made massive changes to the health bureaucracy on his watch, including cutting <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/04/01/hhs-layoff-rfk-staff-cuts\" target=\"_blank\">thousands</a> of jobs and <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/05/states-sue-rfk-hhs-restructuring\" target=\"_blank\">consolidating operations</a>.</li><li>Critics and public health experts <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/07/senators-hhs-cuts-indian-health-services\" target=\"_blank\">have warned the changes</a> and <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/03/27/trump-admin-cancels-state-health-care-grants\" target=\"_blank\">funding cuts</a> put the department's core functions at risk.</li></ul><p><strong>Driving the news: </strong>Kennedy is scheduled to appear before the House panel beginning at 9:30am ET, then testify in front of the Senate HELP committee later in the afternoon.</p><ul><li>The HELP Committee, chaired by Sen. Bill Cassidy (R-La.), requested Kennedy <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/pro/health-care-policy/2025/04/23/rfk-testify-senate-help-may\" target=\"_blank\">appear</a> to discuss the proposed HHS reorganization.</li><li>Kennedy had committed during his confirmation process to brief the committee on a quarterly basis if requested by the chair. </li></ul><p><strong>Zoom out: </strong>Kennedy may also face questioning over his handling of the ongoing measles outbreak. <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/09/measles-cases-1000-us-cdc-rfk-vaccines\" target=\"_blank\">More than 1,000 cases</a> have been recorded across the country, per the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).</p><ul><li>His testimony also coincides with deliberations on the Trump administration's <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/03/trump-budget-low-income\" target=\"_blank\">proposed budget</a>, which requests an <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/05/02/trumps-budget-winners-losers\" target=\"_blank\">$18 billion cut</a> to the <a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/04/09/nih-cuts-nationwide-impact-county-map\" target=\"_blank\">National Institutes of Health</a> among other steep reductions. </li></ul><p><strong>Go deeper: </strong><a href=\"https://www.axios.com/2025/03/31/hhs-rules-enforcement-new-secretary\" target=\"_blank\">HHS ushers in a new enforcement regime</a></p><p><em>Editor's note: This is a developing story. Check back for updates.</em></p>",
